abstract: Nancy O’Malley, Alameda County, Calif, district attorney, announces she will not file criminal charges in 2015 balcony collapse in Berkeley that killed six students from Ireland and injured seven other people; O'Malley says there is insufficient evidence of any criminal negligence.

headline.print_headline: California: No Charges Will Be Filed in 2015 Balcony Collapse in Berkeley
headline.main: California: No Charges Will Be Filed in 2015 Balcony Collapse in Berkeley

snippet: A California prosecutor has decided against filing criminal charges in a fifth-story balcony collapse that killed six students from Ireland and injured seven other people in Berkeley last year.
lead_paragraph: A California prosecutor has decided against filing criminal charges in a fifth-story balcony collapse that killed six students from Ireland and injured seven other people in Berkeley last year.
